Costco Boosts Quarterly Dividend 17%, Announces $4 Billion Buyback Program

-- B y   M a t t   T o w n s e n d
-- 
2011-04-26T21:17:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-26/costco-boosts-quarterly-dividend-17-announces-4-billion-buyback-program.html
Costco Wholesale Corp. (COST) , the largest
U.S. warehouse-club chain, raised its dividend and approved a $4
billion share repurchase program.  The board approved a 17 percent increase in the quarterly
dividend to 24 cents from 20.5 cents, the Issaquah, Washington-
based company said today in a statement. The repurchase program
will expire in April 2015. The current program had $800 million
remaining and will expire in July.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Matthew Townsend in New York at 
 mtownsend9@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Robin Ajello at 
 rajello@bloomberg.net  